BEST friends Lusanda Buthelezi and Phelelani Mbokazi, both nine years old, were inseparable.Their families often joked they would only be separated by death. But on Saturday, the joke came true when a driver lost control of his car and ploughed into the boys. They died at the scene!It&rsquo;s believed the 22-year-old driver had been trying to avoid a pothole when the accident happened. The two young boys were neighbours from Z section in Umlazi, south of Durban. Lusanda&rsquo;s heartbroken mum, Ntombizonke Buthelezi (29), told Daily Sun she was at a hair salon not far from where the accident happened. She said she saw the car swerving towards a group of boys who were walking on the pavement. She said she never thought one of them was her son and that she only realised it when the driver was trying to put him in the car. &ldquo;When I realised that it was my son, I shouted at the driver as I ran to the scene. &ldquo;I couldn&rsquo;t believe my eyes,&rdquo; said Ntombizonke.Phelelani&rsquo;s mum, Fundisiwe (41) said she was still in shock.&ldquo;Phelelani had been so excited and looking forward to being in a new class when schools open tomorrow,&rdquo; she said.The two families said they planned to hold a joint funeral service on Saturday.KZN police spokesman Lieutenant-Colonel Thulani Zwane said Bhekithemba police were investigating a case of culpable homicide. Zwane said a suspect was arrested and appeared in the Umlazi Magistrates Court yesterday.